M1 (my opinion)

here's what i hated about it. bad acting (or bad dialogue? or both), bad pacing/story telling (i was getting real bored), and the physics of everything. (i know it's a fantasy film and to a certain degree you have to be able to buy into the fiction to enjoy it but this was just too horrible that i couldn't) if he can jump that high cuz of the weaker gravity, it means all his muscles are proportionately stronger than everyone else, yet there are scenes where he's being held up by the neck by an individual alien guy. if he could theoretically jump that high, he should also be strong enough to rip 1 alien in half with his bare hands. he should have been kicking way more ass than he did. and just the sheer fact that you see him struggle with the weaker gravity at first,(which mars' gravity isn't that different from earth's so it's ridiculous but i can totally look past that cuz the premise of weaker gravity, therefore superior strength is pretty awesome) but then on the next scene you see him walking like it's normal earth gravity. (ever seen someone walk on the moon? you can't just walk like it's normal gravity even if you tried.) i know i know it's a fantasy movie and you can't enjoy it if you nitpick like i do, but i just couldn't enjoy it cuz of my intuitive understanding of how ludicrous the physics was. i feel like it was lazy film making. they could have tried to make a lil more sense of it in that department.

and to those who say you would like the film more if you read the books, i'm sure that's true, but that doesn't excuse how shitty the film is(in my opinion). a film is a medium in itself and should be enjoyable to everyone whether they read the material or not. i'm sure the book series are superb cuz it's got tons of fans. but this movie is stuck in limbo. only kids could look past all the physics bullcrap, but the original material/plot/characterization is not for kids. ppl blame the marketing for its box office flop and that's probably part of it but it's just a bad movie as well. this is all merely my opinion. if you enjoyed it, that's awesome. more power to you.

on that subject of criticizing the physics, you can also point out that the terminal velocity on such a weak gravity planet would be much slower, thus if one could jump that high, he would float down much more slowly. (like on the moon) if he theoretically did jump that high and land at the speed he did, it would be no different than jumping off a building. there's no reason why he wouldn't break his legs.
as for the movie itself, i definitely thought there were some gratuitous and cool scenes. but for the most, yes it was a little too silly. my little brother enjoyed it though. i think it's a solid film for kids.
